experience.description:
I investigated nitrogen fixation using atmospheric pressure plasma discharges. I used a mix of data-driven methods (regression, Bayesian Optimization) coupled with experimental investigation to study plasma processing. I set up the first wetlab in our group from scratch to investigate plasma-based nitrogen enrichment of manure, and also designed and built a plasma reactor.

Projects included:
i) Using regression to extract physics from experimental plasma data that I generated with co-authors (publication);
ii) Demonstrating plasma treatment of manure enhances the nitrogen content and prevents ammonia loss (publication);
iii) Setup wet-lab in a lab group that was mostly computational (some electronics);
iv) Studied plasma-water contacting and optimized trade-offs musing Multi-Fidelity Bayesian Optimization (MOBO)
v) Analyzed surgical data with a host of machine learning methods, with Random Forest being the most useful

